privacy (https://www.icann.org/epp#privacy)'

privacy (https://www.icann.org/epp#privacy)'
 Based on the provided WHOIS information for the domain "google.com", it appears that this domain is not inherently malicious. The registrant's contact details are associated with a known reputable company, MarkMonitor, Inc., which operates the Whois server in question. Additionally, the domain statuses indicate restrictions such as prohibitions on updates or transfers, but these alone do not necessarily imply malicious intent. However, further investigation would be required to fully assess any potential risks, including an analysis of the domain's history, reputation, and usage patterns. It's also important to note that while ICANN's policies may restrict certain actions, they don't directly correlate with the security status of a domain. Therefore, without additional contextual information, we cannot definitively label "google.com" as malicious solely based on this data.
